# UI Builder Architecture

All user-facing screens are built through the fluent **`UI`** builder API in `io.vepo.kafka.tool.controls.builders.UI`. Views must not construct layout trees with raw JavaFX containers (`GridPane`, `VBox`, `TableView`, `Button`, тАж) except inside the builder implementations themselves.

## Entry point

Use **`UI`** тАФ not `ScreenBuilder`, `GridPane`, or `new TableView` in panes/stages.

| Builder | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `UI.table()` | Standalone data tables |
| `UI.grid()` | Form/dialog grid layout (delegates to `ScreenBuilder.grid()`) |
| `UI.mainView()` | Standard main-window tab content (header + body + action bar) |
| `UI.mainWindow()` | Left-nav shell with tabs |
| `UI.actionBar()` | Refresh / auto-refresh / disconnect row |
| `UI.tableWithEmptyState()` | Table + `EmptyStatePane` stack |
| `UI.section()`, `UI.summaryBar()`, `UI.statCard()` | Cluster monitor sections |
| `UI.twoColumns()`, `UI.verticalSection()`, `UI.scroll()` | Layout helpers |

## Required patterns

### Tables

```java
// тЬЕ GOOD
var table = UI.table()
    .withColumn("Key", KafkaMessage::key)
    .withColumn("Value", KafkaMessage::value)
    .withActions("Actions")
        .button("View", this::openViewer)
        .width(fixedSize(96))
        .add()
    .items(controller.getRows())
    .build();

// тЭМ BAD тАФ raw JavaFX in a pane/stage
var table = new TableView<MessageRow>();
var column = new TableColumn<MessageRow, String>("Key");
```

Legacy grid-embedded tables may still chain `.withColumn("X").fromProperty(...).add()` on `UI.grid().addTableView(n)`; prefer the single-call `withColumn(header, getter)` form for new code.

### Main window tabs

```java
// тЬЕ GOOD
var main = UI.mainWindow()
    .tab("Topics", new TopicsPane(controller))
    .tab("Consumers", new ConsumerGroupsPane(controller))
    .build();

// тЬЕ GOOD тАФ tab content
var view = UI.mainView()
    .title("Topics", "Browse and subscribe to topics.")
    .mainWindowHeader()
    .message(controller.viewMessage())
    .body(UI.tableWithEmptyState(table, controller.getTopics(), "No topics."))
    .actionBar(UI.actionBar().refresh("Refresh", controller::refresh).disconnect("Disconnect", controller::disconnect).build())
    .build();
```

### Stages (dialogs)

```java
// тЬЕ GOOD
var grid = UI.grid()
    .withViewHeader("Browse records", "Fetch by partition and offset.")
    .newLine().addText("Partition");
```

## Layer rules

- **Panes and stages** тАФ compose UI only via `UI.*` builders; wire controller callbacks in lambdas passed to builders.
- **`controls/builders/`** тАФ owns builder implementations (`UI`, `TableBuilder`, `ScreenBuilder`, `ResizePolicy`).
- **Controllers** тАФ no JavaFX node construction; expose observables and actions only.

## When adding UI

1. Extend `UI` or an existing builder before adding ad-hoc layout code to a pane.
2. Update `docs/UI_COMPONENTS.md` when introducing a new builder method or reusable pattern.
3. Do not import `ScreenBuilder` directly in panes/stages тАФ use `UI.grid()` instead.

## Checklist

- [ ] No `new GridPane` / `new TableView` / `new ViewHeader` in panes or stages?
- [ ] Main window assembled with `UI.mainWindow()`?
- [ ] Tab panes use `UI.mainView()` + `UI.table()` / `UI.actionBar()`?
- [ ] Stages use `UI.grid()` for forms?
